===Noun===
'''grille''' or '''grill'''
#A [[rack]]; a [[grid]] of [[wire]] or a sheet of material with a pattern of holes or slots, usually used to [[protect]] something while allowing the passage of [[air]] and [[liquid]]s. Typical uses: to allow air through a [[fan]] while preventing fingers or objects from passing; to allow people to talk to somebody, while preventing [[attack]]. 
#On a [[vehicle]], a [[slot]]ted cover as above, to protect and hide the [[radiator]], while admitting air to cool it.

===Noun===
[[Image:Brazier.JPG|thumb|right|300px|[[brazier|Brazier]] with '''grill''' and pot rest]]
'''grill'''
#A device comprising a source of [[radiant]] [[heat]] and a means of holding food near it, to cook it; a [[barbecue]]; a [[griddle]].
#:''I put some peppers and mushrooms on the '''grill''' to go with dinner.''

===Verb===
'''grill'''
#To [[cook]] food on a [[grill]]; to [[barbecue]].
#:''Why don't we get together Saturday and '''grill''' some burgers?''
#(informal) To [[interrogate]]; to [[question]] [[aggressively]] or [[harshly]].
#:''The [[police]] '''grilled''' him about his movements at the time of the [[crime]].''

